    <item>
      <title>Re: Not a valid ezjscServerRouter argument</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/issues/not_a_valid_ezjscserverrouter_argument/re_not_a_valid_ezjscserverrouter_argument7</link>
      <description>Hi&#13;
&#13;
I checked the problem with ezwebin frontend editing. In fact this is a problem dealing with declared image aliases in &lt;i&gt;image.ini&lt;/i&gt;. &lt;b&gt;reference&lt;/b&gt; alias is not declared by default in ezwebin frontend siteaccess.&#13;
&#13;
So all you have to do is to activate it in your image.ini frontend siteaccess override :&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
    AliasList[]=reference&#13;
&#13;
    [reference]&#13;
    Filters[]&#13;
    Filters[]=geometry/scaledownonly=600;600&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
I updated the doc in SVN :)</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Jérôme Vieilledent)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/issues/not_a_valid_ezjscserverrouter_argument/re_not_a_valid_ezjscserverrouter_argument7</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 08 Oct 2009 17:19:53 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
